    {
      "id": "github-repo-home-node-contract-repo",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "GitHub Repo Node Contract",
      "position": {
        "x": 320,
        "y": 1040
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# GitHub Repo Node Contract\n\nThe GitHub repo node should represent a repository as a first-class Twilite object.\n\nRequired identity:\n- owner\n- repo\n- branch\n- root path or graph path policy\n- optional installation/account context\n\nRequired behaviors:\n- open the repo's landing surface\n- expose repo identity clearly\n- preserve a stable repo address separate from any single file view\n\nRequired surfaces:\n- UI View\n- Icon View\n- Repo Home surface or equivalent named landing surface\n\nImplementation note:\nThe repo node is an integration primitive, not the home surface itself.",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false,
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
