    {
      "id": "github-repo-home-node-contract-home",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Home Node Contract",
      "position": {
        "x": 840,
        "y": 1040
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Home Node Contract\n\nThe home node should be a reusable landing primitive, not a GitHub-specific one.\n\nIt should answer:\n- what is this place?\n- what is it for?\n- where should I go first?\n\nRequired content:\n- title\n- subtitle or framing line\n- short description\n- primary destinations\n- optional supporting destinations\n\nRequired behavior:\n- expose one clear default host-facing surface\n- work for repo roots, product roots, public roots, and internal roots\n\nImplementation note:\nThe home node defines entry semantics. It does not own repo identity by itself.",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false,
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
